description:
CaSCellHandling: Table recording information about handling of cells in a radio access network, including timestamps, cell identifiers, and metadata related to data format and reservation.

dateTime: Timestamp of the record.
Area_Name: Name of the area where the cell is located.
CellId: Unique identifier of the cell.
Id2: Redundant or alternative cell identifier.
Id3:  Ancillary identifier (likely with limited variability).
Id4:  Ancillary identifier (likely indicating a default configuration).
vsDataType:  Data type identifier (specific to Ericsson).
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
CaSCellHandling.caSCellHandlingId:  Identifier for the specific cell handling record (likely redundant with CellId).
CaSCellHandling.reservedBy:  Indicates if the cell handling record is reserved (empty string indicates not reserved).
